# ============================================================
#  .cursorrules — Spring Boot Project
#  Quarks Technosoft Engineering Standards
#  Stack: Java 21 · Spring Boot 3.x · PostgreSQL · Redis · Docker
# ============================================================

## Project Identity
Stack: Java 21 LTS, Spring Boot 3.3, Spring Data JPA, Spring Security 6, PostgreSQL 16, Redis 7
Build tool: Maven (pom.xml) — use Spring Initializr dependencies structure
Architecture: Layered (Controller → Service → Repository) with Domain-Driven Design concepts

---

## PROJECT STRUCTURE

src/main/java/com/quarks/opportunitymapper/
  api/
    controller/      # REST controllers — HTTP layer only
    dto/             # Request/Response DTOs (records preferred)
    mapper/          # MapStruct mappers (DTO ↔ Entity)
    exception/       # @ControllerAdvice global exception handler
  domain/
    model/           # JPA entities
    repository/      # Spring Data JPA repositories (interfaces)
    service/         # Business logic interfaces + implementations
    event/           # Domain events (ApplicationEvent)
  infrastructure/
    config/          # Spring @Configuration classes
    cache/           # Redis cache config and helpers
    external/        # External API clients (Claude, scraper)
    persistence/     # Custom query implementations, specs
  core/
    exception/       # Custom exception hierarchy
    util/            # Pure utility functions (no Spring beans)

src/main/resources/
  application.yml          # Base config (no secrets here)
  application-dev.yml      # Dev overrides
  application-prod.yml     # Prod overrides
  db/migration/            # Flyway migration scripts

src/test/java/
  unit/              # Unit tests — no Spring context (@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension))
  integration/       # @SpringBootTest slice tests
  e2e/               # Full stack tests with TestContainers

---

## JAVA 21 STANDARDS

### Language features — use modern Java
- Records for DTOs: public record ResearchRequest(String companyName, boolean forceRefresh) {}
- Sealed classes for domain variants: sealed interface ResearchStatus permits Pending, Completed, Failed {}
- Pattern matching for instanceof: if (error instanceof RateLimitError rle) { ... }
- Switch expressions (not statements) for multi-branch logic
- Text blocks for multi-line strings (SQL, JSON templates)
- Virtual threads: server.tomcat.threads.virtual=true in application.yml for high concurrency

### Type safety
- Never use raw types — always parameterize generics: List<Company> not List
- Optional<T> for nullable returns from repositories — never return null from a service method
- @NonNull / @Nullable annotations on all public method parameters and return types
- No unchecked casts — use instanceof with pattern matching instead

### Code standards
- All public methods documented with Javadoc (at minimum: @param, @return, @throws)
- Max method length: 20 lines. Extract private helpers if longer.
- Max class length: 200 lines. Split into smaller focused classes if longer.
- Constructor injection only — never @Autowired field injection
- final fields in all @Service and @Component classes

---

## SPRING BOOT ARCHITECTURE

### Controller layer (strict rules)
- Annotate with @RestController @RequestMapping("/api/v1/resource")
- Methods return ResponseEntity<ApiResponse<T>> — never return domain entities
- Validate input with @Valid on @RequestBody — use Bean Validation annotations on DTO records
- No business logic — only: deserialize → validate → call service → serialize
- HTTP methods map to operations: POST=create, GET=read, PUT=full update, PATCH=partial, DELETE=remove
- Use @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.CREATED) for creation endpoints

### Service layer
- Always define an interface: ResearchService with implementation ResearchServiceImpl
- Annotate impl with @Service @Transactional (class level for read-only: @Transactional(readOnly=true))
- Override to @Transactional (readOnly=false) on write methods
- No HTTP types (HttpServletRequest etc.) — accept and return domain objects or DTOs
- Throw typed exceptions — never throw RuntimeException directly

### Repository layer
- Extend JpaRepository<Entity, UUID> — get CRUD and pagination for free
- Custom queries: prefer Spring Data method names for simple queries
- Complex queries: @Query with JPQL (not native SQL unless absolutely necessary)
- Projections: use interface projections to select subset of fields
- Never load full entity graph when only a few fields needed (causes N+1 problems)
- Use @EntityGraph for intentional eager loading — never FetchType.EAGER on associations

### Entity design
- UUID primary keys: @Id @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.UUID)
- Audit fields via @EntityListeners(AuditingEntityListener.class):
  @CreatedDate LocalDateTime createdAt
  @LastModifiedDate LocalDateTime updatedAt
- Soft delete: LocalDateTime deletedAt (null = active). Use @Where(clause="deleted_at IS NULL") on entity
- Use @Column(nullable=false) explicitly — do not rely on DB defaults
- Bidirectional relationships: always manage both sides. Use helper methods on the owning side.
- No @ManyToMany with join table — use explicit join entity with its own ID

---

## API DESIGN

### Consistent response envelope
```java
// ApiResponse.java — ALL endpoints return this
public record ApiResponse<T>(
    boolean success,
    T data,
    String errorCode,
    String message,
    PageMeta meta  // null for non-paginated
) {}
```

### Error handling
```java
// GlobalExceptionHandler.java
@ControllerAdvice
public class GlobalExceptionHandler {
    @ExceptionHandler(AppException.class) // All custom exceptions
    @ExceptionHandler(MethodArgumentNotValidException.class) // Validation
    @ExceptionHandler(Exception.class) // Fallback — log + 500
}
```

### Pagination
- All list endpoints accept: page (0-based), size (default 20, max 100), sort
- Return: Page<T> wrapped in ApiResponse with PageMeta { page, size, total, totalPages }
- Use Pageable from Spring — never manual offset/limit

---

## EXCEPTION HIERARCHY

```
AppException (RuntimeException)
  ├── EntityNotFoundException (404) — "Company 'X' not found"
  ├── ValidationException (422) — input failed business rules
  ├── ConflictException (409) — duplicate resource
  ├── ExternalServiceException (503) — Claude API, scraper failures
  │   └── RateLimitException (429) — with retryAfter field
  └── ForbiddenException (403) — auth passed but access denied
```

- Always include: errorCode (machine-readable), message (human-readable), requestId
- Log at WARN for 4xx, ERROR for 5xx. Always include MDC context (userId, requestId)

---

## SECURITY

- Spring Security 6 with SecurityFilterChain bean (no WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter)
- JWT stateless auth: validate in JwtAuthenticationFilter, set SecurityContext
- Never store JWT in localStorage (frontend) — use HttpOnly cookie
- Method security: @PreAuthorize("hasRole('ROLE_ADMIN')") on sensitive endpoints
- CORS configured in SecurityFilterChain — not in @CrossOrigin annotations
- Sensitive config via Spring Cloud Config or environment variables — never in application.yml committed to git

---

## TESTING

### Unit tests (no Spring context)
- @ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class) — fastest, no context load
- Mock dependencies with @Mock + @InjectMocks
- Test service logic in isolation — mock repositories, external clients
- Naming: methodName_WhenCondition_ShouldExpectedOutcome

### Integration tests (Spring slices)
- @DataJpaTest for repository tests — spins up only JPA context
- @WebMvcTest for controller tests — spins up only web layer
- @SpringBootTest(webEnvironment=RANDOM_PORT) for full stack tests
- TestContainers for real PostgreSQL in integration tests (not H2)
- @Sql annotations for test data setup/teardown

### Coverage targets
- Service layer: 90% line coverage
- Repository layer: 80% (custom queries especially)
- Controller layer: 100% of endpoints tested via MockMvc

---

## PERFORMANCE

- Caching: @Cacheable on service methods for read-heavy data
  Spring Cache with Redis: cache research results, company profiles
  TTL: configure per cache region in CacheConfig
- Async processing: @Async for fire-and-forget operations (email, notifications)
  Configure ThreadPoolTaskExecutor with named pool
- Lazy loading: FetchType.LAZY on all associations by default
  Use @EntityGraph or JOIN FETCH only when you know you need related data
- Query optimization: use EXPLAIN ANALYZE in tests — fail test if query plan uses Seq Scan on large tables

---

## DOCKER
- Multi-stage Dockerfile: maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-21 build + eclipse-temurin:21-jre-alpine runtime
- docker-compose.yml: app, postgres:16, redis:7, pgadmin (dev profile only)
- Health check: GET /actuator/health (Spring Boot Actuator)
- JVM tuning in Dockerfile: -XX:+UseContainerSupport -XX:MaxRAMPercentage=75.0

---

## FILE RULES
- Package declaration matches directory structure exactly
- No business logic in @Configuration classes
- No @Autowired field injection — constructor injection only
- All constants in dedicated Constants class or enum — no magic strings/numbers
- Line 1 comment: // com/quarks/opportunitymapper/[path]/ClassName.java
